# Game Systems

## Core Loop

Calendar ticks drive everything. 1 tick = 1 in-game hour at 1x speed. Speed options: Stop (0) | 1x | 2x | 4x.

Each tick: advance calendar → update dev progress → process sales → decay players → spawn bugs → accrue research → check server load.

At month-end: auto-pause, show MonthlyReport modal, deduct all monthly costs atomically, then wait for player to Resume.

## Systems and Their Config Files

| System | Logic file | Config file |
|--------|-----------|-------------|
| Calendar & tick | `calendarSystem.ts` | `calendarConfig.ts` |
| Game development | `developmentSystem.ts` | `gameConfig.ts` |
| Server/delivery | `serverSystem.ts` | `serverConfig.ts` |
| Fans | `fanSystem.ts` | `gameConfig.ts` |
| Employees | `employeeSystem.ts` | `employeeConfig.ts` |
| Offices | (store actions) | `officeConfig.ts` |
| Skill tree | (store actions) | `skillTreeConfig.ts` |
| Genre/style combos | `calculations.ts` | `genreStyleConfig.ts` |
| Platforms | `calculations.ts` | `platformConfig.ts` |

## Data Flow

Config → pure functions in `lib/game/` → called by Zustand actions in `gameStore.ts` → React components read via selectors.

Components never call game logic directly. They dispatch store actions.
